 <issue
	 id="nks-23"
	 type="purpose"
  linkend="Justification_arm.justification_element"
  category="editorial"
  by="Nigel Shaw"
  date="2002-10-21"
  status="closed">
  <description>
	  Intro says: "Justification represent the identification and description of the reasons why an activity may be required."
	  However activity is not the only thing that could be subject of justification.
	  Suggest change to:
	  "Justification represent the identification and description of the reasons for something. 
	  Justifications may be associated with the data to which they apply.
	  
	  For example: a justification may be provided for a product design. Similarly, a justification may be provided for why an activity is needed or was undertaken."
   </description>
<comment
   by="Kalle Seren" 
   date="2003-01-31">
<description>Text changed as suggested
</description>
</comment>

 </issue>



